value.value: The cardinal ridge that arises distally from the basal cardinal ridge and is oriented distolaterally.
The cardinal ridge that arises distally from the basal cardinal ridge and is oriented distomedially.
The area that is limited posterolaterally by the mediodistal and laterodistal cardinal ridges.
The area that is limited laterally by the mediodistal and basal cardinal ridges.
The area that is limited medially by the laterodistal and basal cardinal ridges.
The anatomical space that is located on the distal cardinal cavity.
The articular porcess that bears the cardinal condyle of the stipes and receives the site of attachment of the tentorio-cardinal muscle.
The fossa that articulates with the basistipital process.
The area that lays parallell with the lateral wall of the prementum.
The sclerite that is on the medial stipital wall, connected to the lacinial lobe and receives the site of insertion of the stipito-lacinial muscle.
The rim that extends along the anterior (dorsal) margin of the medial stipital wall.
The rim that is continuous proximally with the stipital thickening, is located distal to the cardino-stipital hinge and articulates distally with tha basal lacinial sclerite.
The sclerite that is on the medial stipital wall and bears the medial stipital process.
The area that is limited medially by the medial stipital wall and proximolaterally by the margin of the posterior stipital sclerite.

The sclerite that is located on the posterior stipital wall, articulates with the cardo and with the labial palp, is connected by conjunctiva distolaterally to the galeo-lacinial complex, proximally to the hypostoma and the cardo and proximolaterally to the mandible.
The flange that extends along the margin of the posterior stipital wall.
The margin of the posterior stipital sclerite that is concave and accommodates the base of the maxillary palp.
The condyle that articulates with the stipital fossa of the cardo.
The projection that is located distally on the posterior stipital sclerite and encircles the base of the maxillary palp.
The tentorio-stipital muscle that is anterior to the posterior tentorio-stipital muscle.
The tentorio-stipital muscle that is posterior to the anterior tentorio-stipital muscle.
The sclerite that is elongate, paired, is lateral to the cardo and is articulated with the cardo and with the stipes.
The depression that extends medially and adjacent to the medial portion of the principal carina of stipes.
The diameter of the ocellus.

label.value: first sclerite of the maxillary palp

value.value: The sclerite that is ringlike and is connected distolaterally to the posterior stipital sclerite via conjunctiva and muscle.
The maxillary muscle that arises from the posterior stipital sclerite and inserts on the first sclerite of the maxillary palp.

label.value: second sclerite of the maxillary palp

value.value: The sclerite that is ringlike and is connected distally to the first sclerite of the maxillary palp via conjunctiva and muscle.

label.value: third sclerite of the maxillary palp

value.value: The sclerite that is ringlike and is connected distally to the second sclerite of the maxillary palp via conjunctiva.

label.value: fourth sclerite of the maxillary palp

value.value: The sclerite that is ringlike and is connected distally to the third sclerite of the maxillary palp via conjunctiva.

label.value: first intrinsic muscle of the maxillary palp

value.value: The muscle that arises from the first sclerite of the maxillary palp and inserts on the second sclerite of the maxillary palp.

label.value: second intrinsic muscle of the maxillary palp

value.value: The muscle that arises from the first sclerite of the maxillary palp and inserts on the third sclerite of the maxillary palp.

label.value: third intrinsic muscle of the maxillary palp

value.value: The muscle that arises from the second sclerite of the maxillary palp and inserts on the third sclerite of the maxillary palp.
The sclerite that is located on the lateral wall of the lacinial lobe.
The margin of the cranium that is dorsal in frontal view.
The process that corresponds to a single epidermal cell.
The lacinial lobe that is lateral to the inner lobe of the lacinia.
The lacinial lobe that is medial to the outer lobe of the lacinia.
The row of setae that traverses the lacinia along its anterior margin.
The row of setae that traverses the lacinia along its posterior margin.
The row of setae on the lacinial lobe that is marginal.
The conjunctiva that extends along the posterior (dorsal) margin of the premental arm and the proximal margin of the medial stipital wall.

The area of the stipes that is delimited proximomedially by the stipito-premental conjunctiva, proximolaterally by the stipito-mandibular conjunctiva and posteroproximally by the margin of the posterior stipital sclerite.
The sclerite that is located on the lateral wall of the galeo-lacinial complex distaly of the lateral galeal crease and bears the distolateral galeal setiferous patch.
The setiferous patch that is located distolaterally on the galeo-lacinial complex.
The setiferous patch that is located on the lateral wall of the galeo-lacinial complex proximally of the distolateral setiferous patch.
The sclerite that is located on the lateral wall of the galeo-lacinial complex and bears the proximolateral galeal setiferous patch.
The conjunctiva that is between the distolateral and proximolateral galeal sclerites.
The galeal fringe that extends along the distal margin of the distal galeal plate.
The row of setae that extends along the margin of the galeo-lacinial complex, distal to the lacinial lobe.
The galeal fringe that is on the lateral margin of the apicolateral galeal plate.
